Count words in a text file.

This has been built as a single command application, using the Symfony Console component
to do the CLI processing. Application logic is in the Counter\CountWords class.

Ensure you run composer install before running application or tests.

To run:
Example:
  php application.php


Usage:
  app:frequent-words [options] [--] [<path>]

Arguments:
  path                  A path to the text file you wish to count frequently used words in [default: "https://s3-eu-west-1.amazonaws.com/secretsales-dev-test/interview/flatland.txt"]

Options:
  -l, --limit=LIMIT     Show this number of frequent words [default: 100]
  -h, --help            Display this help message
  -q, --quiet           Do not output any message
  -V, --version         Display this application version
      --ansi            Force ANSI output
      --no-ansi         Disable ANSI output
  -n, --no-interaction  Do not ask any interactive question
  -v|vv|vvv, --verbose  Increase the verbosity of messages: 1 for normal output, 2 for more verbose output and 3 for debug

Help:
  This command will count the frequently used words in a text file, located at the path you provide.
